 Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Grand Pré, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France","Boves, Somme, France":"Boves, Somme, Picardie, France","Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France":"Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France","france":"France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Grandpre","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Emile, Pierre, Raoul.","French (<b>Grandpré</b>): topographic name for someone who lived near a large meadow, from French <i>grand</i> ‘large’ + <i>pré</i> ‘meadow’, or a habitational name from Grandpré or Grand Pré, names of several places in various parts of France, named with these words."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Henri","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Germanic.  See  <b>Henry</b> ."],"variants":[{"name":"Henry","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."]}]},{"name":"IV","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["probably a contracted form of  Jep , vernacular form of   Jacob   ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Comte Henri IV de Grandpre was born about 1191, in Grand Pré, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France, his father, Comte Henri III de Grandpré, was 26 and his mother, Melisende de Coucy, was 25. He married Marie DE GARLANDE after 1204. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died on 14 August 1231, at the age of 41."},"et":{"environ 1191–14 août 1231":"umbes 1191–14. august 1231","1191–1231":"1191–1231","1200–1259":"1200–1259","1211–1287":"8.jaanuar1211kuni7.jaanuar1212–1287","1166–1211":"1166–8.jaanuar1211kuni7.jaanuar1212","1167–1221":"1167–1221","14 août 1231":"14. august 1231","AFT 1204":"pärast 1204","1231":"1231","environ 1191":"umbes 1191","1191":"1191","1259":"1259","1211":"8. jaanuar 1211 kuni 7. jaanuar 1212","1167":"1167","1200":"1200","1221":"1221","1166":"1166","1287":"1287","after 1196":"pärast 1197","Grand Pré, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, France":"Grand Pré, Marne, Champagne-Ardenne, Prantsusmaa","Boves, Somme, France":"Boves, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, France":"Montdidier, Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","france":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"environ 1191–14 août 1231":"noin 1191–14. elokuuta 1231","1191–1231":"1191–1231","1200–1259":"1200–1259","1211–1287":"vuodesta8.tammikuuta1211vuoteen7.tammikuuta1212–1287","1166–1211":"1166–vuodesta8.tammikuuta1211vuoteen7.tammikuuta1212","1167–1221":"1167–1221","14 août 1231":"14. elokuuta 1231","AFT 1204":"1204 jälkeen","1231":"1231","environ 1191":"noin 1191","1191":"1191","1259":"1259","1211":"vuodesta 8. tammikuuta 1211 vuoteen 7. tammikuuta 1212","1167":"1167","1200":"1200","1221":"1221","1166":"1166","1287":"1287","after 1196":"1197 jälkeen","Grand Pré, Marne, Champagne-Ardenn